description: Enforce SEO metadata, robots, sitemap, and JSON-LD standards
alwaysApply: true
---

# SEO And Schema Standards

- Every page must provide meaningful metadata (`title`, `description`).
- Document and category metadata should support `{year}` replacement with current year.
- Use canonical URLs for indexable pages.
- `robots.ts` must block technical paths and noisy query patterns.
- `sitemap.ts` must include only published content and use `updatedAt` for `lastModified`.

## Required JSON-LD

- Homepage: `WebSite` (+ `SearchAction`) and `SoftwareApplication`.
- Category page: `BreadcrumbList` and `ItemList` when applicable.
- Document and variation pages: `BreadcrumbList`, `FAQPage`, `HowTo`.

## UX/SEO Coupling

- Keep legal disclaimer visible on site pages and aligned with PDF disclaimer text.
- Ensure server-rendered content remains readable with JavaScript disabled.

## File Scope

- `src/app/page.tsx`
- `src/app/ai-generator/page.tsx`
- `src/app/[category]/page.tsx`
- `src/app/[category]/[document]/page.tsx`
- `src/app/[category]/[document]/[variation]/page.tsx`
- `src/app/robots.ts`
- `src/app/sitemap.ts`
- `src/lib/schema.ts`

## Operational Rules

- Homepage must include `WebSite` and `SoftwareApplication` schemas.
- Category pages must expose indexable metadata and breadcrumb schema.
- Hub/variation pages must include `BreadcrumbList`, `FAQPage`, and `HowTo`.
- `robots.ts` must disallow `/api/`, `/admin/`, `/cabinet/`, `/*?sort=`, `/*?utm_`, `/*?ref=`.
- `sitemap.ts` must not include unpublished documents.

## Done Criteria

- Metadata is unique for homepage, categories, hubs, and variations.
- Schema blocks exist for each route type and serialize as valid JSON.
- `npm run build` succeeds and generates `robots.txt` and `sitemap.xml`.
